In addition, the type of work performed exerts a lot of influence on maternity, although less on the timing of mating," explains CSIC researcher Margarita Delgado.
The level of education is another factor that differentiates the age of women when they get married and when they have the first offspring.
According to the survey, the higher the educational level, the higher the age at which they marry and at which they have the first child.
There is also a difference between women of the same generation.
